============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

Theorem/Law:  Golden Ratio
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 = 1.618...
Applications: Art, architecture, nature, design
Discoverer:   Ancient Greeks (500)

Theorem/Law:  Godel's Incompleteness
Branch:       Logic
Formula:      Every consistent system has unprovable true statements
Applications: AI limits, foundations of math
Discoverer:   Kurt Godel (1931)

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

